1135
01:14:30,754 --> 01:14:31,936
I'm a very brave man.

1136
01:14:36,523 --> 01:14:37,636
Oh, hold on, buddy.

1137
01:14:37,740 --> 01:14:40,381
You got plenty of time for that.

1138
01:14:40,486 --> 01:14:41,668
I love you.

1139
01:14:41,773 --> 01:14:42,815
I love you too, mom.

1140
01:14:42,920 --> 01:14:44,204
Let me talk to Jake, OK?

1141
01:14:51,678 --> 01:14:52,601
He's OK, Corrine.

1142
01:14:52,616 --> 01:14:53,574
I know.

1143
01:14:53,589 --> 01:14:54,597
I can hear that.

1144
01:14:54,702 --> 01:14:58,107
Jake, thank you.

1145
01:14:58,212 --> 01:15:00,610
You don't have to thank me.

1146
01:15:00,715 --> 01:15:05,372
Campbell and I are even.

1147
01:15:05,476 --> 01:15:06,728
Jake, what direction you heading?

1148
01:15:06,832 --> 01:15:08,291
West. Why?

1149
01:15:08,396 --> 01:15:10,203
There's supposed be a Salter
diesel truck heading west,

1150
01:15:10,307 --> 01:15:12,045
but it's late. We need that fuel.

1151
01:15:12,149 --> 01:15:14,896
I just saw Salter truck going east,

1152
01:15:15,000 --> 01:15:16,181
heading away from you guys.

1153
01:15:16,286 --> 01:15:18,023
What did he say?

1154
01:15:18,127 --> 01:15:20,735
Jake, you run that bastard down.

1155
01:15:20,839 --> 01:15:21,839
Do you hear me?

1156
01:15:21,916 --> 01:15:23,932
You get that truck here to this plant.

1157
01:15:24,036 --> 01:15:27,964
If we don't get that diesel fuel here,
we lose everything.

1158
01:15:28,068 --> 01:15:32,239
And I mean everything for 100 miles.

1159
01:15:32,343 --> 01:15:33,804
Do you understand me?

1160
01:15:33,908 --> 01:15:35,854
I gotcha.

1161
01:15:45,864 --> 01:15:47,567
Unconfirmed reports have

1162
01:15:47,671 --> 01:15:49,723
at least two tornadoes hitting
the Helman-Klein nuclear power

1163
01:15:49,827 --> 01:15:51,007
plant.

1164
01:15:51,111 --> 01:15:53,023
Significant damage has been sustained,
but as of yet

1165
01:15:53,127 --> 01:15:54,170
there are no details.

1166
01:15:54,275 --> 01:15:55,387
No way.

1167
01:15:55,491 --> 01:15:56,491
Storm watch warnings remain

1168
01:15:56,534 --> 01:15:57,959
in effect until further notice.

1169
01:15:58,064 --> 01:15:59,064
No way am I turning around,
not for this kind of pay.

1170
01:16:06,753 --> 01:16:09,394
We're losing that water too fast.

1171
01:16:09,498 --> 01:16:12,035
He's not going to have enough time.

1172
01:16:46,480 --> 01:16:49,991
Corrine, we're losing 250 gallons a minute.

1173
01:16:50,094 --> 01:16:51,659
Even with the hoses, we're still losing

1174
01:16:51,763 --> 01:16:52,763
more than we're putting in.

1175
01:16:55,586 --> 01:16:56,907
Can you get more hoses in there?

1176
01:16:57,010 --> 01:16:58,958
We'll have to save one
hose for the diesel fuel.

1177
01:17:03,371 --> 01:17:06,222
Gail, how's Potter coming on
switching those water pumps

1178
01:17:06,326 --> 01:17:08,690
